Maina was reportedly attacked while heading home from his shop at the shopping centre.
Led by Senator John Kinyua, the people held protests and demanded heightened security, citing the recent attack of a man they said was nursing serious injuries at Nyahururu County Referral Hospital.
They said the man went through a similar ordeal.
“The businessman is well known in this area. Residents are yet to come to terms with the murder,”  Mr Kinyua said on Saturday.



