Mr Daniel Gachanja, who chairs the business community in the area, noted that the population has increased but the number of police officers at a nearby station remains small.
Marmanet Assistant Commissioner Philip Chesa said investigations will establish the motive for the attack.
“We have launched an investigation and will ensure the killers are brought to book,” said Mr Chesa.
He urged residents to always volunteer information that can help arrest criminals.
The body was taken to the Nyahururu County Referral Hospital mortuary.
